<body>

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>The Art of Folding</h1>
        </header>
        <main>
            <article>
                <h2>Some Rules</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>It does not matter how strong your hand is - your opponent needs to ahve enough bluff combos to
                        make bluffcatchers a call</li>
                    <li>Player profiling is super important!</li>
                    <li>Always try to find the bluff combos in each spot yourself and ask how difficult they are to find
                    </li>
                    <li>Always try to find the value combos as well - if there is a lot of value relative to bluffs,
                        it's almost always a fold</li>
                    <li>If you see almost no value but also no bluffs, weight the fact that it's harder to find bluffs
                        over the lack of value and lean towards folding</li>
                    <li>We all make mistakes - use them as lessons to improve</li>
                    <li>Always consider their value range relative to the properties of your hand, and determine if
                        those properties help or hurt you</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Another good way to increase our blue-line is to find high-level folds in spots where most player
                    would call down</p>

            </article>
        </main>
    </div>

</body>

</html>
